# CSS Version Query Rule

When you **change any CSS that is loaded via `styles.css`**, always bump the query-version in the HTML link tag so browsers won't use a stale cached file.

## Required behavior

- Whenever you edit `styles.css` (or another main stylesheet for the docs site), you **must**:
  - Find the `<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css?v=...">` tag in the relevant HTML file (for example `index.html`).
  - Increment or change the `v` query parameter (e.g. `v=1.0.1` → `v=1.0.2`).
- The new version can be any monotonic change (you don't need semantic versioning), but it **must be different** from the previous one.

## Example

```html
<!-- ❌ BEFORE (old version in HTML after CSS change) -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css?v=1.0.1">

<!-- ✅ AFTER (version bumped to break browser cache) -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css?v=1.0.2">
```

Use this pattern consistently so that every CSS edit is paired with a version bump in the HTML.

